                <title><alert>Teacher's Role</alert></title>
                <p xml:id="auto_d810acmb">
                    Collect and review the exit tickets to gauge Learner understanding and identify any common misconceptions that need to be addressed in the next lesson.
                </p>
            </li>
            <!-- <p xml:id="auto_5gvicwh9">
                Students complete individually to demonstrate understanding.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_wn9tkfn2">
                <alert>Question 1:</alert> A motorist left Nakuru for Nairobi, a distance of <m>240</m> km, at 8:00 AM and travelled at an average speed of <m>90</m> km/h. Another motorist left Nairobi for Nakuru at 8:30 AM and travelled at <m>100</m> km/h. Find: (a) The time they met. (b) How far from Nairobi they met.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_7q484tbb">
                <alert>Question 2:</alert> A cyclist is riding towards a motorcyclist on a straight road. The cyclist travels at <m>15</m> km/h and the motorcyclist at <m>45</m> km/h. If they are initially <m>100</m> metres apart, how long will it take for them to meet?
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_4rzodab8">
                <alert>Answer Key (teacher reference):</alert>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_wed5kv78">
                <ol marker="1.">
                    <li xml:id="auto_spmfqqfy">(a) First motorist travels <m>45</m> km in 30 min. Remaining distance = <m>195</m> km. Relative speed = <m>190</m> km/h. Time <m>\approx 1.03</m> hours. They meet at approximately 9:32 AM. (b) Second motorist travels <m>\approx 103</m> km, so they meet <m>\approx 103</m> km from Nairobi.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_y2sgck4d">Relative speed = <m>60</m> km/h = <m>\frac{50}{3}</m> m/s. Time = <m>\frac{100}{\frac{50}{3}} = 6</m> seconds.</li>
                </ol>
            </p> -->
        </axiom>

        <exercises xml:id="exercises-objects-moving-towards-same-directions">
            <exercise xml:id="auto_xvw3h9tg">
                <statement>
                    <p xml:id="auto_i3793sc6">
                        A motorist left Nakuru for Nairobi, a distance of <m>240</m> km, 
                        at 8.00 am. and travelled at an average speed of <m>90</m>
                        km/h. Another motorist left Nairobi for Nakuru at <m>8.30</m> <em>am</em>. 
                        and travelled at <m>100</m> <em>km/h</em>. Find:
                        <ol xml:id="auto_uns7uy7a" marker="(i).">
                            <li xml:id="auto_pznncs1p">
                                <p xml:id="auto_vdaqr0oo">
                                    The time they met.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li xml:id="auto_io7c7mg5">
                                <p xml:id="auto_1ia5h6us">
                                     How far from Nairobi they met.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p xml:id="auto_j3d9g59z">
                        The time taken for the two motorists to meet after 8.30 am is given by:
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \amp = \frac{195 \, km}{190 \, \text{km/h}} </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = 1.0263 \, \text{hours} </mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    <p xml:id="auto_jbix7gsd">
                        Therefore, the two motorists meet at:
                        <md>
                            <mrow>8:30 \, \text{am} + \text{1 hour and 1.58 minutes} \amp = 9:31.58 \, \text{am} </mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    <p xml:id="auto_udgsxrp3">
                        The distance traveled by the second motorist before the meeting is:
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \amp = 100 \, km/h \times 1.0263 \, \text{hours} </mrow>
                             <mrow> \amp =  102.63 \, \text{km} </mrow>
                        </md>
                       
                    </p>
                    <p xml:id="auto_hjs3biho">
                        Thus, they met approximately <m>102.63</m> km from Nairobi.
                    </p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>

             <exercise xml:id="auto_tvcyazg4">
                <statement>
                    <p xml:id="auto_9iebte5y">
                        A train travels from Mombasa to Nairobi, a distance of <m>500</m> <em>km</em>, 
                        at a speed of <m>90</m> <em>km/h</em>. 
                        If a second train starts <m>1</m> hour later from Mombasa and travels at a 
                        speed of <m>120</m> km/h, 
                        after how much time will the second train overtake the first one?
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p xml:id="auto_6cqiqp47">
                        The time taken for the second train to overtake the first train is given by:
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \amp = \frac{90 \, km}{30 \, \text{km/h}} </mrow>
                            <mrow> \amp = 3 \, \text{hours} </mrow>
                        </md>

                    </p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>

             <exercise xml:id="auto_dzpxvjgg">
                <statement>
                    <p xml:id="auto_qcprbyp4">
                        A matatu left town <m>A</m> at <m>7</m> <em>am</em> and travelled towards a town 
                        <m>B</m> at an average speed of <m>60</m> <em>km/h</em>. 
                        A second matatu left town <m>B</m> at <m>8</m> <em>am</em> and travelled towards town 
                        <m>A</m> at <m>60</m> <em>km/h</em>. 
                        If the distance between the two towns is <m>400</m> <em>km</em>, find:
                        <ol xml:id="auto_5lftwgir" marker="a.">
                            <li xml:id="auto_h2l3rqr1">
                                <p xml:id="auto_zckcwelh">
                                    The time at which the two matatus met.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li xml:id="auto_ilczrvb1">
                                <p xml:id="auto_y3msb0vp">
                                    The distance of the meeting point from town <m>A</m>.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p xml:id="auto_8z7o1cv1">
                        <ol xml:id="auto_ozb1gaz8">
                            <li xml:id="auto_0rkdq4bu">
                                <p xml:id="auto_57g8onnr">
                                    The time taken for the two matatus to meet after 8 am is given by:
                                    <md>
                                        
                                        <mrow> \amp = \frac{340 \, km}{120 \, \text{km/h}} </mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp = 2.8333 \, \text{hours} </mrow>
                                    </md>
                                </p>
                                <p xml:id="auto_55nfn2g3">
                                    Therefore, the two matatus meet at:
                                    
                                     <m>8:00 \, \text{am} + \text{2 hours and 50 minutes} = 10:50 \, \text{am} </m>
                                    
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li xml:id="auto_be7x63tb">
                                <p xml:id="auto_3lo5vegx">
                                    The distance traveled by the first matatu before the meeting is:
                                    <md>
                                        <mrow> \amp = 60 \, km/h \times 2.8333 \, hours </mrow>
                                         <mrow> \amp =  170 \, km </mrow>
                                    </md>
                                </p>

                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>

            <exercise xml:id="auto_vgdm7ygi">
                <statement>
                    <p xml:id="auto_4c3x52vj">
                        A cyclist is riding towards a motorcyclist on a straight road. The cyclist travels at 
                        <m>15</m> <em>km/h</em> and the motorcyclist at <m>45</m> <em>km/h</em>. 
                        If they are initially <m>100</m> meters apart, how long will it take for the motorcyclist 
                        to overtake the cyclist?
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p xml:id="auto_9hus34kh">
                        The relative speed is <m>60</m> <em>km/h</em> <m> = \frac{50}{3}</m> <em>m/s</em>.
                    </p>
                    <!-- <p xml:id="auto_k8pn6o0x">
                        Converting to <em>m/s</em>, we get <m>60 \times \frac{1000}{3600} = 16.67</m> <em>m/s</em>.
                    </p> -->
                    <!-- <p xml:id="auto_z0cl6p7q">
                        The time taken to overtake is <m>\frac{100}{\frac{50}{3}} = 6</m> seconds.
                    </p> -->
                    <p xml:id="auto_z0cl6p7q">
                        The time taken to overtake is <m>6</m> seconds.
                    </p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>

            <exercise xml:id="auto_94v904ke">
                <statement>
                    <p xml:id="auto_zn51u2rq">
                        Two cars, <m>A</m> and <m>B</m>, are traveling on parallel roads. 
                        Car <m>A</m> moves at a speed of <m>50</m> <em>km/h</em> and car <m>B</m> 
                        moves at <m>70</m> <em>km/h</em>. 
                        If car <m>B</m> is <m>150</m> meters behind car <m>A</m>, 
                        how long will it take for car <m>B</m> to overtake car <m>A</m>?
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p xml:id="auto_ohgh14bv">
                        The relative speed is <m>20</m> <em>km/h</em> <m>= \frac{5}{18}</m> <em>m/s</em>.
                    </p>
                            <!-- <p xml:id="auto_00vrgbkw">
                                Converting to <em>m/s</em>, we get <m>20 \times \frac{1000}{3600} = 5.56</m> <em>m/s</em>.
                            </p> -->
                    <!-- <p xml:id="auto_vvr7f2ln">
                        The time taken to overtake is <m>\frac{150}{\frac{5}{18}} = 540</m> seconds.
                    </p> -->
                    <p xml:id="auto_vvr7f2ln">
                        The time taken to overtake is <m>540</m> seconds.
                    </p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>

        </exercises>

        <axiom component="lesson-plan">
            <title>Differentiation Strategies</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_x9a6p5go">
                <alert>For Struggling Learners:</alert>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_piokqgh6">
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_jkiq2iji">Provide step-by-step calculation sheets with formulas already written.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_05dz8pai">Use visual aids showing objects moving toward each other with arrows.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_8bezigxz">Allow use of calculators for conversions and calculations.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_houx9vsc">Pair with peer tutors during practice.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_p7bcbarx">Create a comparison chart: Same Direction vs Different Directions.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_lkweeeec">
                <alert>For Advanced Students:</alert>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_pm6avhni">
                <ul>
                    <li xml:id="auto_5pjymsu8">Solve problems involving three objects moving in different directions.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_j7g568vx">Calculate meeting times with different starting times.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_1oxv6qk3">Explore real-world applications: trains, aircraft, ships.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_8fx38t0x">Create their own relative speed problems for classmates to solve.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_2kf33z7j">Investigate what happens when objects start from different positions.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </axiom>

        <axiom component="lesson-plan">
            <title>Extension Activity: Train Journey Investigation</title>
            <p xml:id="auto_slsij9ao">
                Two trains are travelling on the same track toward each other. Train A leaves Mombasa at 8:00 AM travelling at <m>80</m> km/h toward Nairobi. Train B leaves Nairobi at 9:00 AM travelling at <m>100</m> km/h toward Mombasa. The distance between Mombasa and Nairobi is <m>500</m> km.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_bbswokj6">
                <ol marker="1.">
                    <li xml:id="auto_kyghey9h">Calculate the relative speed of the two trains.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_hk509q1f">Determine at what time the two trains will meet.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_kyj3s79m">Find how far from Mombasa they will meet.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_9sv385gr">Create a distance-time graph showing both trains.</li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_wsx0710q">Explain what would happen if Train B left at 8:00 AM instead of 9:00 AM.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </axiom>

